awesome—let’s lock the *build plan* first. Below is a combined **business-systems analyst + technical** blueprint for a PWA that guides Israeli SMBs through VAT/Income-Tax/NI setup, licensing, renewals, and recurring compliance. I’ve included **authoritative deep links**, **data sources**, **UI/UX rules**, and a **step-by-step delivery plan** using 2025 updates.

---

# 1) Core scope & user jobs (MVP)

**Target users**

* Solo self-employed (עוסק פטור / עוסק מורשה), micro-Ltds (חברה בע״מ קטנה), service trades that may need a Business License (רישוי עסקים).

**Top jobs the app must do**

1. **“Open my business properly” wizard**

   * Decide “Exempt” vs “Authorized” VAT dealer, list documents, open files, and link to the right online forms (VAT 821, NI self-employed, etc.). ([Government of Israel][1])
2. **Business Licensing (רישוי עסקים)** eligibility & path finder by activity + location. ([Government of Israel][2])
3. **Compliance calendar** (VAT/withholding/NI deadlines) with push reminders. (15th/16th/23rd rules; 2025 schedule). ([Government of Israel][3])
4. **“What docs do I need right now?”** (bank proof, ID, lease, etc.), with dynamic checklist mapped to the chosen path (e.g., VAT-821). ([Government of Israel][4])
5. **Renewals & updates** (change dealer details, close VAT file, license renewals). ([Government of Israel][5])

**Why now**

* 2025 updates: VAT rate is **18%** (since Jan 1, 2025). Israel is phasing in **e-invoicing allocation numbers** and a **reference number** requirement—your app can keep SMBs compliant. ([dglaw.co.il][6])

---

# 2) Canonical sources & deep links (use in product)

**Identity & accounts**

* **Gov National Login (הזדהות לאומית / MyGov):** info + login entry points your UX should link to before sending users to any secured gov service.

  * MyGov hub: [https://my.gov.il/](https://my.gov.il/) (identity required) ([my.gov.il][7])
  * National e-ID FAQ / signup: ([Government of Israel][8])

**Taxes & VAT**

* **VAT authorized dealer (Form 821) – open online** (English & Hebrew service pages): ([Government of Israel][1])
* **Exempt dealer – open online:** ([Government of Israel][9])
* **Verify dealer status (online lookup):** ([Government of Israel][10])
* **VAT topic hub (change details, closure, etc.):** ([Government of Israel][5])
* **Monthly deadlines (rules):** 15/16/23 guidance (official). ([Government of Israel][3])

**National Insurance (ביטוח לאומי)**

* **Self-employed registration & criteria:** pages with 2025 thresholds & how-to. ([www.btl.gov.il][11])
* **Single flow (Tax Authority + NI) announcement (2024→ live):** one digital process to open both files. ([www.btl.gov.il][12])
* **NI personal area:** ([ps.btl.gov.il][13])

**Business Licensing (רישוי עסקים)**

* Gov landing + “Business Licensing Revolution” explainer; use to pre-screen activities needing a license & which ministries approve. ([Government of Israel][2])
* **Apply for a business license** (online handoff to municipality): ([Government of Israel][14])
* **Open data (who needs a license) dataset**—can power your eligibility checker & content. ([data.gov.il][15])

**Companies / Partnerships**

* **Corporations Authority** (basic free extracts; paid full extracts). Use API datasets for prefill/validation. ([Government of Israel][16])

**Legal & privacy (what your app must follow)**

* **Privacy Protection (Data Security) Regs (2017)** English explainer + official text (applies to any personal-data DB). ([Government of Israel][17])
* **Amendment 13 (2025 updates):** new duties (DPO/DSO triggers, rights notices). Use in privacy design. ([DataGuidance][18])
* **Accessibility**: Israeli **IS-5568** (WCAG 2.0 AA baseline; Part 1 updated 2023; guidance 2025). Your PWA must comply & publish an accessibility statement. ([Government of Israel][19])

---

# 3) Product requirements (BRD-style)

## 3.1 User stories (priority)

* As a **new self-employed**, I answer a few questions and get:
  (a) the correct VAT path (exempt/authorized) with **Form 821** or **exempt flow**,
  (b) NI registration steps, and
  (c) a dynamic checklist + deep links. ([Government of Israel][1])
* As a **café owner**, I see if I need a **Business License**, which “Approval Authorities” apply (e.g., Health Ministry), required docs, fees, SLA, and **apply** at the right municipal portal. ([Government of Israel][20])
* As an **active dealer**, I get a **compliance calendar** with push alerts for **15th/16th/23rd** & special postponements, plus quick links to file. ([Government of Israel][3])
* As a **Ltd**, I can fetch my **basic company info** (via datasets) to prefill forms. ([data.gov.il][21])

## 3.2 Functional scope (MVP)

* **Eligibility & pathfinder engine**: inputs (business activity, revenue estimate, location, employees soon/none), outputs (dealer type, license need, next actions, documents). (Sources above.)
* **Doc checklist generator** mapped to each step (e.g., bank proof for 821). ([Government of Israel][4])
* **Smart deep-link launcher** (SSO first → target service): MyGov → VAT/NI/License. ([my.gov.il][7])
* **Compliance calendar** with Israel-specific rules, holidays, and per-user cadence (monthly/bi-monthly). ([Government of Israel][3])
* **Knowledge cards** (short, authoritative): VAT 18% since 1-Jan-2025; e-invoice ref/allocation roadmap (explain simply). ([dglaw.co.il][6])
* **Company lookup autofill** (basic data from ICA datasets). ([data.gov.il][22])

## 3.3 Non-functional

* **Accessibility**: IS-5568 Part 1 (WCAG 2.0 AA) RTL first; accessibility statement page. ([Government of Israel][19])
* **Privacy & security**: classify DB according to Israeli regs; role-based access, encryption at rest, incident logbook, DSR (access/correct). ([Government of Israel][23])
* **Offline-first PWA**: service worker caching for guides, checklists, and saved tasks; sync queue for reminders.
* **Localization**: HE (default) + EN/RU later; fully RTL-aware typography, numerals, forms.

---

# 4) Technical architecture (high-level)

**Front end (PWA)**

* **Next.js + React** (App Router), **TypeScript**, **RTL** support, **Service Worker** (Workbox).
* **State**: Redux Toolkit/Query or TanStack Query for server cache; Zod for schema validation.
* **Storage**: IndexedDB (idb) for offline checklists, setups, calendar; local encrypted vault for tokens (WebCrypto).

**Back end**

* **API**: Node.js (NestJS or Express), TypeScript.
* **Data**: Postgres (user profiles, checklists, schedules, audit); Redis (jobs/queues for reminders).
* **Integrations (read-only / deep link)**

  * **Gov services**: we *don’t* impersonate; we **route** users to official flows after SSO (links above).
  * **Open data**: pull and cache **ICA** company datasets & **Business Licensing** dataset for eligibility search. ([data.gov.il][21])
* **Compliance calendar engine**: rules encoding (15/16/23 + postponements) with an override table per official notices. ([Government of Israel][3])
* **Content pipeline**: admin CMS (Headless—e.g., Strapi) for Hebrew micro-guides; keep citations per card.

**Security/Privacy**

* **Pseudonymous IDs**; separate PII; encrypted at rest; access logging; annual risk assessment in line with **Data Security Regs**; if Amendment 13 thresholds hit (DB scope/sensitivity), appoint DPO/DSO. ([Government of Israel][17])

---

# 5) UI/UX—what “great” looks like (Israel-specific)

**Foundations**

* **Government UX principles & service-design** patterns (clear language, stepwise flows, mobile-first). ([National-Digital-Agency][24])
* **Israeli Government Design System** references (layout rhythm, inputs, alerts). ([National-Digital-Agency][25])
* **Accessibility**: Hebrew RTL, keyboard order, focus states, form labels, contrast; publish **Accessibility Statement**. ([Government of Israel][26])

**Key screens**

1. **Entry quiz (60–90s)** → instantly shows: dealer type suggestion, NI step, licensing need. (Include an upfront “This uses official gov rules & links.”)
2. **Action plan** (kanban cards): “Open VAT file”, “Register NI”, “Check license”. Each card opens: “What you need” → “How to do it” → **“Go to gov service” link** (SSO prompt). ([Government of Israel][1])
3. **Compliance calendar** with color codes + auto reminders (choose monthly/bi-monthly); tooltips cite the **15/16/23** rules. ([Government of Israel][3])
4. **Licensing checker**: choose activity & city → show whether **Business License** is needed, who approves, and the relevant **municipal portal** link. ([Government of Israel][20])
5. **Knowledge cards** (e.g., VAT 18% in 2025; e-invoice: “reference” required from 2025; allocation numbers thresholds 2026-2028). ([dglaw.co.il][6])

---

# 6) Data model (starter)

* **User**: id, language, business_stage, city, consent, accessibility_needs.
* **BusinessProfile**: type (self-employed/Ltd), dealer_suggestion, activity_code(s), municipality_id, employees (y/n).
* **Task**: key (vat_open_821, ni_register, license_check…), status, deps, deadline_rule (e.g., “15th VAT”), deeplink_url, required_docs[].
* **ComplianceRule**: code (VAT_PERIODIC, WITHHOLDING, VAT_DETAILED), rule_text, official_source_url. ([Government of Israel][3])
* **DatasetCache**: ica_company_basic, business_licensing_catalog (with update_at + source). ([data.gov.il][21])

---

# 7) Build steps (end-to-end)

**Sprint 0 — governance & compliance**

1. Approve **legal basis** (consent + legitimate interest), draft **Privacy Notice** reflecting **Data Security Regs & Amendment 13** rights; appoint roles if scope requires. ([Government of Israel][23])
2. Accessibility plan per **IS-5568**; define testing (screen readers, keyboard nav) + **Accessibility Statement** page. ([Government of Israel][19])

**Sprint 1 — MVP skeleton**
3) Next.js PWA scaffolding (HE RTL), Service Worker (Workbox), IndexedDB cache, auth-less first release.
4) Content studio (Strapi) + “knowledge cards” with **inline citations** to gov pages.

**Sprint 2 — Eligibility & checklists**
5) Encode **dealer decision** logic (inputs: projected revenue, sector flags that force “authorized”) and NI triggers; surface docs needed for **Form 821** and exempt flow. ([Government of Israel][1])
6) Add **NI registration** guidance (multi-annual report, or the new single flow). ([www.btl.gov.il][27])

**Sprint 3 — Licensing**
7) Activity → license need decision using **Business Licensing** dataset + ministry approval map; link to **apply** service. ([data.gov.il][15])

**Sprint 4 — Compliance calendar**
8) Implement deadline rules (15/16/23) + per-month 2025 dates + holiday adjustments table. Push notifications and iCal export. ([Government of Israel][3])

**Sprint 5 — Company data autofill (nice-to-have)**
9) Basic company info lookup from **ICA** datasets to prefill forms (name, number, status). ([data.gov.il][22])

**Sprint 6 — Quality & release**
10) **A11y** audit (IS-5568 AA), Hebrew content proofing; privacy & security review per Israeli regs. ([Kol Zchut][28])

---

# 8) QA & compliance checklists

**Functional**

* [ ] VAT pathfinder returns **correct** result for edge sectors; 821 doc list matches the official service page. ([Government of Israel][4])
* [ ] NI flow shows both **single digital process** and **multi-annual report** fallback. ([www.btl.gov.il][12])
* [ ] Licensing checker points to the right **municipal** application & approval authorities list. ([Government of Israel][20])
* [ ] Calendar dates match **gov rules**; postponements are applied when announced. ([Government of Israel][3])

**Legal/privacy**

* [ ] Data map + risk assessment per **Data Security Regs**; DSR workflows (access/correct) exposed in UI per **Amendment 13**. ([Government of Israel][17])

**Accessibility**

* [ ] IS-5568 AA: forms, focus, contrast, errors, RTL; publish **Accessibility Statement**. ([Government of Israel][26])

---

# 9) Future: e-invoicing bridge (Phase 2)

* Educational card + optional helper for the **Reference Number (2025)** and **Allocation Number** thresholds (15k→10k→5k 2026-2028), with links to official docs; do **not** submit on user’s behalf—just guide & checklist. ([KPMG][29])

---

# 10) Known constraints & decisions

* **No scraping / impersonation** of gov flows—only **deep links** after **MyGov** authentication. ([my.gov.il][7])
* **Content changes**: centralize in CMS with **citations** (Gov.il pages get updated; your app must version your guidance). ([Government of Israel][30])
* **Where facts differ** (e.g., VAT deadlines moved due to holidays), the **official gov notice** takes precedence. ([Government of Israel][3])

